<h3>Blogs</h3>
<p>If you use a blog on the site, you should be aware that any personally identifiable information you submit there can be read, collected, or used by other users of these forums, and could be used to send you unsolicited messages. We are not responsible for the personally identifiable information you choose to submit in these forums.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="margin-bottom:15px;">Security</h3>
<p>The network uses industry standard security measures to protect against the loss, misuse, and alteration of personal information under their control. Although they make good faith efforts to maintain the security of such personal information, they cannot guarantee that it will remain free from unauthorised access, use, disclosure, or alteration. Further, while they work hard to ensure the integrity and security of their network and systems, they cannot guarantee that their security measures will prevent "hackers" or other unauthorised persons from illegally accessing or obtaining your information.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Ning and Curtin University does not assume any liability to third parties whose information is included in your Address Book, or which you post or transmit in any Content on a Ning Network. To help maintain the security of your Studentbox ID, please keep your password secure.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Once you’ve created a profile you will also be asked to create a unique username and password that must be entered each time you, or one of our employees that has a business need to access the information, logs on to one of our products via the site. These safeguards help prevent unauthorised access, maintain data accuracy, and ensure the appropriate use of all data.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>While Curtin University and the Ning Network strive to protect your personal information, no data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be totally secure and therefore we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you send to us. You send any information via the site at your own risk.</p>
